the number of nuclei over time-

00:11:54.810 --> 00:11:58.310
that's the rate expression,
or the rate law-- k,

00:11:58.310 --> 00:12:01.490
the decay constant, times
the number of nuclei.

00:12:01.490 --> 00:12:04.900
And because activity is
proportional to the number

00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:08.230
of nuclei, we can also
take this expression

00:12:08.230 --> 00:12:11.600
that we had before
